result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Willie Laqu Hambright not in court, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. appeared by video for Willie Laqu Hambright.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Status Conference. Defendant not produced. Defense counsel informs court that they are still awaiting discovery materials and an offer from the State. Further, defense requests an additional status conference date. Court grants requests and adjourns matter to Br 16.
Status conference scheduled for November 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

11:09 AM Defendant Willie Laqu Hambright appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. appeared by video for Willie Laqu Hambright.  Prosecuting attorney Gregg Herman in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Milwaukee County Sheriff Detective R. Richards. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 16.
Status conference scheduled for October 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Willie Laqu Hambright not in court, in custody in MSDF.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. appeared by video for Willie Laqu Hambright. Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case is set for a Preliminary Hearing. Defense Counsel requests an adjournment due to caseload. Case is adjourned. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Willie Laqu Hambright not in court, defendant in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness was present. Mr Hambright was present by video from MSDF prior to the case being called on the record. Attorney Klimetz does not appear. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 6, 2022 at 10:00 am.
State Public Defender - Order Appointing Counsel received and filed.  bm
Time of Preliminary Hearing changed from 8:30 to 10:00.  ADA and defense attorney notified.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Defendant Willie Laqu Hambright in court with attorney Evan Barrett Weitz.  Defendant Willie Laqu Hambright in custody at MSDF.  Amy E Spanczak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Willie Laqu Hambright appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Grayson, Branch 16. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 28, 2022 at 10:00 am.
